  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide reading opportunities to schoolchildren</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Books in Burkina Faso are more often than not too expensive for the average citizen, especially for those who live in rural areas and depend on agriculture for their livelihood. Using a tricycle motorbike with a wagon on the back, FAVL has developed a mobile library that can provide schoolchildren with reading materials in rural Burkina Faso. The books have been locally purchased, and will allow residents of the villages to develop their reading and critical thinking skills.</narrative>
  </description>
